                {
                    "__type__": "Note",
                    "fields": [
                        "Who is known as the 'father of medicine'?",
                        "<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading mw-first-heading\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow: visible; border: 0px; font-size: 1.8em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; flex-grow: 1;\"><span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">Hippocrates</span></h1><div><span class=\"mw-page-title-main\"><br></span></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><b>Hippocrates</b> (c. 460 – c. 370 <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/BC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"BC\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">BC</a>) was a <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Greece\" title=\"Ancient Greece\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Greek</a> <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_doctor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Medical doctor\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">doctor</a> who is called the \"father of <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine\" title=\"Medicine\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">medicine</a>\". He was the first person to teach that people got sick for <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science\" title=\"Science\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">scientific</a> reasons. Previously, people believed that <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease\" title=\"Disease\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 102, 204); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">disease</a> was caused by angry gods.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><br></p><div><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"font-size: 12.32px; border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); border-spacing: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); color: black; margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 1em; padding: 0.2em; clear: right; line-height: 1.5em; width: 22em; font-family: sans-serif;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Born</th><td class=\"infobox-data\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">c. 460 BC<br><div class=\"birthplace\" style=\"display: inline;\"><a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kos\" title=\"Kos\" style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 102, 204);\">Kos</a>, <a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Greece\" title=\"Ancient Greece\" style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 102, 204);\">Ancient Greece</a></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Died</th><td class=\"infobox-data\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">c. 370 BC<br><div class=\"deathplace\" style=\"display: inline;\"><a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larissa\" title=\"Larissa\" style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 102, 204);\">Larissa</a>, Ancient Greece</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Occupation</th><td class=\"infobox-data role\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician\" title=\"Physician\" style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 102, 204);\">Physician</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Era</th><td class=\"infobox-data category\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_Greece\" title=\"Classical Greece\" style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(51, 102, 204);\">Classical Greece</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" class=\"infobox-label\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Title</th><td class=\"infobox-data title\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">The Father of Western Medicine</td></tr></tbody></table><br></div><div>Ref:- https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippocrates<br></div>"
                    ],
                    "guid": "PFij*0&SxR",
